This paper is primarily focused on neural architecture search (NAS) and its overfitting issue, which is a common problem in machine learning and deep learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the use of reinforcement learning and policy gradient methods, which are commonly used in the field of neural networks and deep learning, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another likely category. Finally, the paper also mentions experiments related to face recognition, which falls under the category of cs.CL (Computation and Language).
